---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Testimonial from '../components/Testimonial.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Zero Fluff"
  description="Meet Andy Doyle. 30+ years of digital product experience, now focused on practical AI implementation."
>
  <!-- Section 1: Hero -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow stack">
      <h1>About Zero Fluff</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted">
        I'm Andy Doyle. I live in Totnes, Devon, and I've spent 30+ years
        building digital products. Now I help small businesses make AI work
        for them -- properly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: The Story -->
  <section class="section reveal" style="background-color: var(--color-border);">
    <div class="container narrow stack">
      <h2>The Short Version</h2>
      <p>
        I've been building digital products since the early days of the web. Over three
        decades, I've founded companies, shipped software, and learned -- mostly the hard
        way -- what works and what's just noise.
      </p>
      <p>
        I created Filmily, a video sharing platform. I built SelectCommerce, an e-commerce
        system. I founded Shiift, a file transfer service. Each one taught me something
        about building things that people actually use, not things that just look good in
        a pitch deck.
      </p>
      <p>
        A couple of years ago, I noticed something. Businesses everywhere were being
        told that AI would change everything. And it can -- but not the way most consultants
        sell it. The gap between "AI is amazing" and "here's how it helps your specific
        business" was enormous. And nobody seemed to be filling it.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's why I started Zero Fluff. I take my experience building real products and
        apply it to AI implementation. No hype, no buzzwords, no fifty-slide presentations.
        Just working tools that make your business better.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Track Record -->
  <section class="section reveal">
    <div class="container narrow stack">
      <h2>What I've Built</h2>
      <p>
        Over 30 years, I've built products across video, e-commerce, and file transfer.
        The thread connecting all of it: making technology useful for real people.
      </p>
      <ul class="track-record stack">
        <li>
          <strong>Filmily</strong> -- A video sharing platform built when video on the web
          was still a headache. Taught me how to ship products that handle real-world scale.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>SelectCommerce</strong> -- An e-commerce system for businesses that needed
          more than a template. Built to be flexible without being complicated.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Shiift</strong> -- A file transfer service designed to make sending large
          files painless. Still running, still useful.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The common theme? Building things that work, not things that just sound impressive.
        That same principle drives everything I do with AI implementation today.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Testimonials -->
  <!-- Placeholder testimonials -- replace with real ones -->
  <section class="section reveal" style="background-color: var(--color-border);">
    <div class="container stack-lg">
      <div class="narrow stack">
        <h2>What Clients Say</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid-2">
        <Testimonial
          quote="Andy automated our weekly reporting and saved us about 8 hours a week. No fuss, no jargon -- he just got on with it and it worked from day one."
          name="Sarah Mitchell"
          role="Operations Director"
          company="Apex Logistics"
        />
        <Testimonial
          quote="I'd wasted months trying to figure out AI on my own. Andy sat down with me, understood my business in an hour, and built exactly what I needed. I finally get what AI can actually do for us."
          name="James Cooper"
          role="Founder"
          company="Bright Path Digital"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: CTA -->
  <CTA />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .track-record {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .track-record li {
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
